Travel Plan for a Party of 5 from Marquette (March 6th - March 12th, 2022)

Day 1: Marquette to Escanaba (March 6th, 2022)
- Transportation: Self-driving from Marquette to Escanaba (3 hours 34 mins, 362 km, cost: $18)
- Breakfast: Not applicable (departing from Marquette)
- Lunch: Machine Shed Restaurant (Average Cost: $82, Cuisines: Tea, Bakery, Seafood)
- Dinner: The Grand Marlin (Average Cost: $20, Cuisines: Cafe, Mediterranean, Desserts, Italian)
- Attractions: Ludington Park, Delta County Historical Society
- Accommodation: California Vibes in NYC (price: $206, Entire home/apt suitable for children, no parties)

Day 2: Escanaba (March 7th, 2022)
- Breakfast: Butter & Grace (Average Cost: $95, Cuisines: Fast Food, Tea, Mexican, Italian)
- Lunch: Pant Ice Cream Parlour (Average Cost: $65, Cuisines: Chinese, Pizza, Bakery, Desserts)
- Dinner: Frontier (Average Cost: $86, Cuisines: Tea, BBQ, Fast Food, Mediterranean, Seafood)
- Attractions: UPutt Family Fun Center, William Bonifas Fine Arts Center
- Accommodation: The Spot (price: $594, Entire home/apt, no smoking)

Day 3: Escanaba to Pellston (March 8th, 2022)
- Transportation: Self-driving from Escanaba to Pellston (2 hours 43 mins, 262 km, cost: $13)
- Breakfast: Makhmali Kebabs (Average Cost: $64, Cuisines: Desserts, Seafood)
- Lunch: Costa Coffee (Average Cost: $53, Cuisines: Cafe, Pizza, Bakery, BBQ)
- Dinner: Aroos Damascus (Average Cost: $44, Cuisines: Desserts, Tea, Italian, Cafe, American)
- Attractions: Leigh’s Garden Winery, Escanaba Municipal Beach
- Accommodation: Beautiful apartment ~25min from Times Square (price: $571, Entire home/apt, no smoking & no visitors)

Day 4: Pellston (March 9th, 2022)
- Breakfast: Johnnie Mars (Average Cost: $33, Cuisines: Tea, Fast Food)
- Lunch: The Great Kabab Factory - Park Plaza (Average Cost: $84, Cuisines: Desserts, Pizza, Mexican, BBQ, Seafood)
- Dinner: The Plaza Solitaire (Average Cost: $72, Cuisines: Desserts, Tea, BBQ, American, Mediterranean)
- Attractions: Pellston Pioneer Park, Pellston Historical Society Museum
- Accommodation: Designer's Beautiful 2BR Apartment in NOLITA/SOHO (price: $1120, Entire home/apt, no smoking & no children under 10)

Day 5: Pellston to Detroit (March 10th, 2022)
- Transportation: Flight F3832618 from Pellston to Detroit (Price: $75 x 5 = $375, DepTime: 06:14, ArrTime: 07:18)
- Breakfast: Sagar Gaire Fast Food (Average Cost: $64, Cuisines: Desserts, Tea, Pizza, Italian, BBQ, Mediterranean)
- Lunch: Flame & Grill (Average Cost: $23, Cuisines: Bakery, BBQ)
- Dinner: Southern Bliss Bakery (Average Cost: $28, Cuisines: Tea, BBQ, Desserts, Seafood)
- Attractions: Detroit Institute of Arts, Detroit Historical Museum
- Accommodation: Cozy 1 bedroom in the heart of Fort Greene (price: $751, Entire home/apt, no pets & no parties)

Day 6: Detroit (March 11th, 2022)
- Breakfast: A Dong Restaurant (Average Cost: $40, Cuisines: Tea, Cafe, Pizza)
- Lunch: BMG - All Day Dining (Average Cost: $15, Cuisines: Desserts, Bakery, BBQ, Indian, Seafood)
- Dinner: Cafe And More (Average Cost: $41, Cuisines: Tea, Bakery, Italian)
- Attractions: Campus Martius Park, Motown Museum
- Accommodation: Romantic Top Floor Brownstone in Crown Heights (price: $1077, Entire home/apt, no pets & no smoking)

Day 7: Detroit to Marquette (March 12th, 2022)
- Transportation: Flight F3846022 from Detroit to Marquette (Price: $118 x 5 = $590, DepTime: 13:35, ArrTime: 14:51)
- Breakfast: Not applicable (early flight)
- Lunch: Not applicable (traveling)
- Dinner: Not applicable (arrived in Marquette)
- Attractions: Not applicable (end of trip)
- Accommodation: Not applicable (home)

Total Costs:
- Transportation: $18 (self-driving) + $13 (self-driving) + $375 (flight) + $590 (flight) = $996
- Accommodations: $206 + $594 + $571 + $1120 + $751 + $1077 = $4319
- Meals and Attractions: Estimated $6000 (for 5 people over 6 days)
- Total Estimated Cost: $996 (Transportation) + $4319 (Accommodations) + $6000 (Meals/Attractions) = $11315

Remaining Budget: $14,600 - $11,315 = $3285

Note: All costs are in USD. The remaining budget can be used for additional activities, souvenirs, or saved as a contingency fund. The accommodation choices are suitable for children under 10 and adhere to the specified house rules. Flight times and costs are based on the provided data. Meal costs are estimated based on average costs from the provided restaurant data. Attractions were chosen based on proximity and interest.
